description:
## User Story
As a developer, I want globals.css and tailwind.config.ts updated with the correct dark mode tokens so that all components inherit the correct neutral dark palette automatically.

## Why
The current dark mode has blue-tinted backgrounds (222.2 84% 4.9%) and is missing semantic tokens (success, warning, card, popover, sidebar, shadows, gradients). These foundational files are the single source of truth — fixing them fixes all shadcn/ui components instantly.

## What to Change

### File: src/app/globals.css

Replace the entire .dark block with the delivery framework's neutral palette. The current .dark uses blue-gray values; switch to pure neutral grays. Keep indigo as brand color but fix surfaces and backgrounds.

Target .dark CSS variable values:
```css
.dark {
  --background: 0 0% 7%;
  --foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --card: 0 0% 10%;
  --card-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --popover: 0 0% 10%;
  --popover-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --primary: 243 75% 68%;        /* lighter indigo visible on dark bg — was 210 40% 98% */
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
  --secondary: 0 0% 15%;
  --secondary-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --muted: 0 0% 15%;
  --muted-foreground: 0 0% 65%;
  --accent: 0 0% 15%;
  --accent-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --destructive: 0 62.8% 50.6%;
  --destructive-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --border: 0 0% 18%;
  --input: 0 0% 15%;
  --ring: 243 75% 68%;
  --success: 142 76% 45%;
  --success-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
  --warning: 45 93% 55%;
  --warning-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
  --gradient-subtle: linear-gradient(180deg, hsl(var(--background)), hsl(0 0% 10%));

  /* Sidebar dark */
  --sidebar-background: 0 0% 7%;
  --sidebar-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --sidebar-primary: 243 75% 68%;
  --sidebar-primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
  --sidebar-accent: 0 0% 15%;
  --sidebar-accent-foreground: 0 0% 98%;
  --sidebar-border: 0 0% 18%;
  --sidebar-ring: 243 75% 68%;
}
```

Also add to the :root (light mode) if missing: --success, --success-foreground, --warning, --warning-foreground, --card, --card-foreground, --popover, --popover-foreground, --sidebar-* variables (copy from delivery framework light mode values).

### File: tailwind.config.ts

Add missing color tokens to the colors section:
```ts
success: { DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--success))', foreground: 'hsl(var(--success-foreground))' },
warning: { DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--warning))', foreground: 'hsl(var(--warning-foreground))' },
card: { DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--card))', foreground: 'hsl(var(--card-foreground))' },
popover: { DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--popover))', foreground: 'hsl(var(--popover-foreground))' },
sidebar: {
  DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--sidebar-background))',
  foreground: 'hsl(var(--sidebar-foreground))',
  primary: 'hsl(var(--sidebar-primary))',
  'primary-foreground': 'hsl(var(--sidebar-primary-foreground))',
  accent: 'hsl(var(--sidebar-accent))',
  'accent-foreground': 'hsl(var(--sidebar-accent-foreground))',
  border: 'hsl(var(--sidebar-border))',
  ring: 'hsl(var(--sidebar-ring))',
},
```

Also extend the theme with shadow variants from the delivery framework:
```ts
boxShadow: {
  elegant: '0 10px 30px -10px hsl(var(--primary) / 0.15)',
  card: '0 1px 3px 0 hsl(220 20% 25% / 0.1), 0 1px 2px 0 hsl(220 20% 25% / 0.06)',
}
```

## Edge Cases
- The .dark primary is changing from white to lighter indigo — verify primary buttons still look good in dark mode
- If tailwind.config.ts already has card/popover tokens, don't duplicate
- Sidebar vars should fall back gracefully if no sidebar component exists

## How to Verify
1. Switch to dark mode in the app
2. Background should be near-pure black (#121212 range), NOT blue-black
3. Cards should be slightly lighter than background (#1a1a1a range)
4. Primary buttons should show indigo (not white) on dark bg
5. Run yarn build — no TypeScript errors

## User Story
As a user signing in, I want to land on a clean /dashboard URL with no stray query parameters, so the browser URL bar is not confusing and the auth code is not exposed unnecessarily.

## Why
After OAuth login, the dashboard URL shows ?code=<value>. This is caused by the middleware (middleware.ts lines 66-70): when it sees an authenticated user on /sign-in, it clones req.nextUrl and changes the pathname to /dashboard — but req.nextUrl.clone() copies ALL query params, including any code= that was on the sign-in URL.

## What to Change
File: src/middleware.ts, lines 66-70

Current code:
```ts
if (pathname.startsWith("/sign-in") && session) {
  const redirectUrl = req.nextUrl.clone();
  redirectUrl.pathname = "/dashboard";
  return NextResponse.redirect(redirectUrl);
}
```

Fix — clear all search params before redirecting:
```ts
if (pathname.startsWith("/sign-in") && session) {
  const redirectUrl = req.nextUrl.clone();
  redirectUrl.pathname = "/dashboard";
  redirectUrl.search = "";
  return NextResponse.redirect(redirectUrl);
}
```

That is the only change needed. Do not touch anything else in middleware.ts.

## Edge Cases
- redirectUrl.search = "" clears ALL query params, which is correct — we never want /sign-in params (redirect, error, code) carried into /dashboard
- The redirect query param used by the middleware to bounce users back after auth (line 54) is read before this block runs, so clearing it here has no side effect

## How to Verify
1. Sign out, then click sign in with Google and complete OAuth
2. After landing on dashboard, confirm URL is exactly /dashboard with no query params
3. Confirm existing session redirect still works (visit /sign-in while already logged in → lands on /dashboard with no params)
